        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Joe Biden finishes his presidential term with an eventful final week as president. He signed off with a <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-18-01-2025-r1-3-farewell-speech" target="_blank">farewell speech</a> warning that an “oligarchy is taking shape” which threatens American democracy. Biden leaves a divided legacy in his single term as president. His term underwent a series of challenges, including Covid 19 and its devastation, the Ukraine War, and the Middle East troubles. He also had his share in the realization of the Israel-Hamas ceasefire deal. Biden will spend the last day of his presidency in Charleston, South Carolina. He secured a major victory in this state during the <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-18-01-2025-r1-3-2020-presidential-campaign" target="_blank">2020 presidential campaign</a>, which drove him into the Democratic nomination and presidency.</p>
