        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">This week, the world’s largest religious festival, the <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-18-01-2025-r2-5-maha-kumbh-mela" target="_blank">Maha Kumbh Mela</a>, began in Prayagraj, India. Over the next six weeks, it is expected to attract an estimated 400 million Hindu pilgrims who bathe in the sacred rivers for spiritual purification. Prayagraj, formerly Allahabad, was renamed in 2018 to emphasize its spiritual significance for Hindu pilgrims. The Maha Kumbh Mela has required years of planning and substantial investment to accommodate the millions of visitors expected in the city, typically 6 million residents. This year’s event features extensive safety measures, including AI-powered security cameras and drones.</p>
        </mj-text>
