        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">This week, there were confirmation hearings of Trump’s selections, the most controversial of which was on Tuesday for Pete Hegeth. Senator Tammy Duckworth challenged him in International Relations and <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-18-01-2025-r3-6-called-him-unqualified" target="_blank">called him unqualified</a>. Attorney General nominee Pam Bondi refused to directly <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-18-01-2025-r3-7-acknowledge-trump-2020-loss" target="_blank">acknowledge Trump’s 2020 loss</a>, drawing scrutiny but unlikely Republican opposition. Secretary of State nominee Marco Rubio suggested Ukraine may need to make concessions to end its war with Russia. Interior nominee Doug Burgum endorsed Trump’s “energy dominance” agenda, emphasizing innovation over regulation. EPA nominee Lee Zeldin acknowledged climate change as accurate but avoided committing to regulating greenhouse gas emissions, citing economic concerns.</p>
